                    "description": "Growing global human populations and prosperity will require progressively more resources in the coming decades, putting further pressure on biodiversity. Simultaneously, international pledges and legislation for nature conservation are becoming increasingly ambitious. My research builds fundamental scientific understanding of the linkages between land-use and biodiversity in agro-commodity landscapes, to address the challenge of combining growing resource production with ambitious nature conservation targets. I do this by quantifying the implications of resource production on wildlife populations and behaviour, while using and developing innovative wildlife monitoring techniques.",
